ategy which allows us to capture different\nbijections. These two approaches should be seen as two complementary ways of\nunifying bijections between planar maps and decorated trees.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 May 2013 20:07:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 Oct 2014 07:33:14 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 12 May 2015 13:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-27"}
